This paper presents a new method for online reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper focuses on continuous state and action Markov decision processes, which are commonly studied in robotics and control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control systems and optimization, which are covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
